                        <p style="margin-bottom: 50px">Kitty was born and raised in the beautiful and vibrant city of Vancouver and has watched as the city has transformed itself into a major metropolitan centre over the past twenty years.</p>
                        <p>Kitty attended Simon Fraser University where she obtained a Bachelor's Degree in Business Administration with a concentration in Marketing. After working for a decade in corporate business and luxury retail, Kitty pursued her second passion in education. She returned to Simon Fraser University to obtain her Bachelor of Education degree and a Post-Baccalaureate degree in Early Childhood Education. Kitty has an abundance of experience working with people and helping to grow and build communities. Through many years of teaching part-time fitness classes at Killarney Community Centre, her high school community centre, she has helped people achieve their fitness goals and assisted them in realizing the value of living a healthy lifestyle. She continues to stay true to her roots by supporting her community.</p>
                    </div>
